                                     [--task-file TASK_FILE] [--file FILE]
                                     [--dir DIRECTORY] [--output OUTPUT]
                                     [--format FORMAT] [--recursive]
                                     [--dry-run] [--verbose] [--parallel N]
                                      

positional arguments:
  task_name             Task name (e.g., RestingEyesOpen)
  input_path            EEG file or directory to process

options:
  -h, --help            Show help
  --task TASK           Task name (alternative to positional)
  --task-file TASK_FILE
                        Python task file to use
  --file FILE           Single EEG file to process (alternative to positional)
  --dir, --directory DIRECTORY
                        Directory containing EEG files to process (alternative
                        to positional)
  --output OUTPUT       Output directory (default: workspace/output)
  --format FORMAT       File format glob pattern for directory processing
                        (default: *.{raw,set}). Examples: '*.raw', '*.edf', '*.set'.
                        Note: '.raw' will be auto-corrected to '*.raw'
  --recursive           Search subdirectories recursively
  --dry-run             Show what would be processed without running
  --verbose, -v         Enable verbose/debug output
  --parallel, -p N      Process files in parallel (default: 3 concurrent
                        files, max: 8)
